[{"id":"VR039389","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title text-left\">The population pyramids illustrate the age and sex structure of China’s and Nigeria’s populations.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<ol class=\"ordered_list style:3\">\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Using the population pyramids, describe one difference in the age structure of China compared to that of Nigeria.</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Describe one governmental policy that influenced the age structure in China.</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Describe one economic consequence of the age structure of Nigeria.</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Describe one economic consequence of the age structure of China.</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Explain a political consequence of having a disproportionately younger population structure.</li>\n</ol>\n","rubricRef":"VR039389_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"The figure presents a population pyramid titled “China, 2014.” The left side of the population pyramid represents male population, and the right side represents female population.  Population is measured along the horizontal axis, in millions, from 0 to 65 in increments of 13. The ages 0 through 100 and over are represented in groups of 4 along the vertical axis. The pyramid has a narrow top, is broad in the center and narrows slightly at the base. The data in the pyramid are as follows. Note that all values are approximate. The shape of the pyramid is relatively symmetrical about the vertical axis. From ages 0 through 19, the male population hovers between 40 and 50, and the female population hovers between 36 and 40. From ages 20 through 29, the male population increases to 60, and the female population increases to 50. From ages 30 to 39, the male population decreases to 50, and the female population decreases to 45. From ages 40 to 49, the male population increases to 63, and the female population increases to 58. From ages 50 to 100 and over, the population for both males and females decreases steadily until it reaches nearly 0.\" height=\"347\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR039389.g01.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n\n<p class=\"caption\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"caption\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a population pyramid titled “Nigeria, 2014.” The left side of the population pyramid represents male population, and the right side represents female population.  Population is measured along the horizontal axis, in millions from 0 to 15 in increments of 3. The ages 0 through 100 and over are represented in groups of 4 along the vertical axis. The pyramid has a broad base and a narrow top. The data in the pyramid are as follows. Note that all values are approximate. The shape of the pyramid is symmetrical about the vertical axis. The largest age group is 0 through 4, peaking at 15 million for male population and between 12 and 15 million for female population. Both male and female populations decrease gradually for each age group, ending at just above 0 for the 100 plus age group.\" height=\"347\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR039389.g02.png\" width=\"500\" /></p>\n"}]}]